### Expense Approval Pipeline - Version A (Durable Functions) test scenarios
### Run with the REST Client VS Code extension. Base URL assumes `func start` locally.
### For the scenarios that need a manager decision, copy the `instance_id` from the 202 response.

@base = http://localhost:7071/api
@instance_id = PASTE_INSTANCE_ID_HERE

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1. Valid expense under $100 -> auto-approved
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{base}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Alice Johnson",
  "employee_email": "alice@example.com",
  "amount": 42.50,
  "category": "supplies",
  "description": "USB-C hub for new laptop",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2. Valid expense >= $100, manager will approve
###    Step 2a: submit; Step 2b: approve using returned instance_id
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{base}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Alice Johnson",
  "employee_email": "alice@example.com",
  "amount": 450.00,
  "category": "travel",
  "description": "Taxi + conference registration",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### 2b. Manager approves (replace @instance_id at top of file)
POST {{base}}/expenses/{{instance_id}}/decision
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "decision": "approve",
  "approver": "bob.manager@example.com",
  "comment": "Approved - within team budget"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3. Valid expense >= $100, manager will reject
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{base}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Charlie Davis",
  "employee_email": "charlie@example.com",
  "amount": 2500.00,
  "category": "equipment",
  "description": "Second 4K monitor",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### 3b. Manager rejects
POST {{base}}/expenses/{{instance_id}}/decision
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "decision": "reject",
  "approver": "bob.manager@example.com",
  "comment": "Not in this quarter's budget"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4. Valid expense >= $100, no manager response -> escalated
###    Do NOT send a decision. Wait APPROVAL_TIMEOUT_SECONDS (default 60s).
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{base}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Dana Kim",
  "employee_email": "dana@example.com",
  "amount": 199.99,
  "category": "software",
  "description": "Annual JetBrains license",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5. Missing required fields -> validation error
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{base}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Eve Lee",
  "amount": 75.00,
  "category": "meals"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6. Invalid category -> validation error
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{base}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Frank Wu",
  "employee_email": "frank@example.com",
  "amount": 30.00,
  "category": "gambling",
  "description": "Team building",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### Utility: query orchestration status
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
GET http://localhost:7071/runtime/webhooks/durabletask/instances/{{instance_id}}?taskHub=ExpenseApprovalHub&connection=Storage
